10.20   Find World Writable Files
Implementation Steps 
1. 
Remove the following path components if they exist in the root users $PATH: 
current working directory ('.') 
empty directories („::‟) 
a trailing path separator at the end of the $PATH (‘:’) 
any directory with world or group -write permissions set 
Note: If the files returned in the script output or audit file output are application-generated files Thus , for 
application-generated files the users and groups are assigned by the application itself, Administrator cannot change 
the user or group for these files. Hence, for these files created by the application, the control can be considered as not 
applicable. 

